                            <article class="bg-content p-3 rounded">
                                <h1 class="fs-4 fw-bold mb-3">DMCA Notice &amp; Copyright Policy</h1>
                                <p>This site is a volunteer-operated companion guide for <strong>HER TREES : PUZZLE
                                        DREAM</strong>,
                                    the hand-drawn point-and-click adventure created and published by Stone and
                                    officially
                                    released on February 11, 2026. We host editorial text, links, and legally shared
                                    assets to
                                    help players understand the game before visiting the official storefronts. All
                                    trademarks,
                                    characters, screenshots, and promotional copy remain the exclusive property of
                                    Stone.</p>

                                <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold mb-2">Respecting Rights Holders</h2>
                                <p>We never post executable builds, soundtrack downloads, or premium art packs. When we
                                    reference
                                    official images we credit Stone and only use low-resolution thumbnails permitted
                                    under fair
                                    use for commentary. If you are a rights holder and would like us to revise or remove
                                    something, contact us immediately.</p>

                                <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold mb-2">How to Submit a Valid DMCA Notice</h2>
                                <p>Email <a href="mailto:dmca@hertrees.co">dmca@hertrees.co</a> with the subject line
                                    &quot;DMCA Notice&quot; and provide:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Your full legal name and physical or electronic signature.</li>
                                    <li>An identification of the copyrighted work you believe has been infringed (a list
                                        is fine
                                        if multiple works are affected).</li>
                                    <li>The exact URL(s) on hertrees.co that contain the disputed material.</li>
                                    <li>Your preferred contact information (email, phone number, and mailing address).
                                    </li>
                                    <li>A statement that you have a good-faith belief the challenged use is not
                                        authorized by the
                                        copyright owner, its agent, or the law.</li>
                                    <li>A statement, made under penalty of perjury, that the information in the notice
                                        is accurate
                                        and that you are the copyright owner or authorized to act on the owner's behalf.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>We will confirm receipt within one business day and generally resolve takedown
                                    requests within
                                    forty-eight hours by removing or editing the referenced content.</p>

                                <h2 class="fs-5 fw-bold mb-2">Counter Notices</h2>
                                <p>If you believe your material was removed in error, reply to our takedown confirmation
                                    email with
                                    evidence of your authorization to use the content and a statement consenting to
                                    jurisdiction
                                    in your local federal court. We may restore the content 10 business days after
                                    receiving a
                                    complete counter notice unless the complaining party informs us that legal action
                                    has been
                                    filed.</p>

                                <p class="small text-secondary mt-3">Reminder: Submitting false DMCA notices or counter
                                    notices
                                    can carry legal consequences. When unsure, reach out using
                                    <a href="mailto:support@hertrees.co">support@hertrees.co</a> so we can clarify how a
                                    piece of
                                    material was sourced before filing.
                                </p>
                            </article>
